Importantly, the inclusion of two different types of spatial transmission channels allows us to test for additionalities in the spatial dynamics of the epidemic diffusion in Germany. When we interpret the resulting spatial effects, we carefully account for the relationship between the two weighting schemes \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
