				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\left( {u_{i,t - p} } \right)$$\end{document}ui,t-p is statistically significant and positive in all cases. This points to the fact that the COVID-19 dynamics in Germany is significantly determined by local hot spots that antecede the infection development in their broader geographical neighborhood. When we accordingly apply the SP-ECM approach for hot spot detection, Fig. 2 plots the resulting spatial distribution of the long-run adjustment coefficient \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
